         <abstract>
            <p>A collection of miracles worked
            by the Trinity, in which
            a wondrous story follows a homily, for each
            day of the week. One of the types of the collections known as the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2388Taamme">Miracles of the Trinity</ref>
            </p>
            <p>Three miracles published by
               Turaev (1912: 322ff.) originate from this kind of
               Trinity miracles. One short miracle (mss. Conti
               Rossini 53, ff. 32v–33v, and 62, ff. 132ra–va)
               seems to be the same text as in the 15th-cent. ms.
               VatLib Aeth. 89, f. 28rv (GréTisVat 357). It
               is found also in orient. 409, fol. 61ra–va (Six-
               Deu 310) and EMML no. 1882, fol. 61v (text in
               Turaev 1912: 322f.). The same collection is preserved
               in mss. VatLib Aeth. 177 (fols. 5–57v) and
               180. Turaev (1917: 83ff.) summarizes its second,
               fi fth and seventh miracles.</p>
         </abstract>
